> solved by sy_chen and Roundgod (2:53 +1)

Thanks to the typesetting of sample test case, we may discover some periodicity: there is a 0 for every four digits. It is not something heretical but simply because of the square factor 4. This inspires us the solution: we may filter all potential value of answer modulo 4, 9, 25, 49, 121, 169, then use the Chinese remainder theorem to obtain the candidate answers. For each candidate answer, we may check it by enumerating all possible squares of prime numbers. Note that if there are too many candidates the answer must be no.

